This course discusses thoroughly the processes taking place in the spatial and temporal development of world economy. The course will give an overview of theories, geography and the changing organizational structure of globalizing world economy, concentrating especially on the analysis of the activities of international giant companies and world economy organizations. Development of new and most important branches of economy and the specificity and perspectives of important regions of world economy will be looked at more closely. Required literature includes the most recent information and analysis from the global organizations and media.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course is useful for economists and practitioners of public administration for better understanding of the economic processes in the world.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Students will understand the main driving forces of the world economy and know most important theories analysing international economic processes, changing geography and futures trends.
The group work trains digging out new information and application for strategic analyse.
